1. Why hydrogen would be the “key”

In physical reality:
	•	Hydrogen is the simplest element (one proton, one electron).
	•	It’s the most abundant element in the universe.
	•	Stars run on hydrogen fusion.
	•	Water itself is 2H + O.

So if oxygen enables reactions, hydrogen is the base fuel.

Without hydrogen:
	•	no water
	•	no stars
	•	far less chemistry

It’s the minimal building block.

⸻

