Many systems—physics, math, computing—tend to organize around a similar ladder:
	1.	Simple primitives
	2.	Combinations
	3.	Emergent structures

Examples:
	•	bits → software
	•	atoms → molecules
	•	letters → language
	•	neurons → thoughts

